    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p>Effective Date: April 2024</p>

    <p>Welcome to BuildWell! This Privacy Policy describes how BuildWell collects, uses, and protects your personal information when you use our website or services. We are committed to respecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information.</p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>

    <p>When you interact with BuildWell, we may collect the following types of information:</p>

    <ol>
        <li><strong>Personal Information</strong>: When you make a purchase or sign up for an account, we may collect personal information such as your name, email address, shipping address, and payment details.</li>
        <li><strong>Transactional Information</strong>: We collect information about your transactions with us, including details about the products you purchase.</li>
        <li><strong>Device and Usage Information</strong>: We may automatically collect certain information about your device and how you interact with our website, such as your IP address, browser type, and browsing behavior.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>

    <p>We use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p>

    <ul>
        <li>Processing Orders: To fulfill and process your orders, including shipping products to your address and processing payments.</li>
        <li>Communications: To communicate with you about your orders, respond to your inquiries, and provide customer support.</li>
        <li>Improving Our Services: To analyze trends and preferences, improve our website, and develop new products and services.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>

    <p>At BuildWell, we take your privacy seriously. We do not share, sell, or disclose your personal information to third parties except in the following circumstances:</p>

    <ol>
        <li><strong>Service Providers</strong>: We may share your information with trusted service providers who assist us in operating our website, conducting our business, or servicing you.</li>
        <li><strong>Legal Compliance</strong>: We may disclose your information to comply with applicable laws and regulations, to respond to a subpoena, search warrant, or other lawful request for information we receive, or to otherwise protect our rights.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Data Security</h2>

    <p>We implement reasonable security measures to protect your personal information and maintain its confidentiality. However, please note that no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure.</p>

    <h2>Your Choices</h2>

    <p>You have the right to access, correct, or delete your personal information. You may also opt out of receiving marketing communications from us by following the unsubscribe instructions provided in our emails.</p>

    <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>

    <p>BuildWell's website is not directed to individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 18 years of age.</p>

    <h2>Updates to This Privacy Policy</h2>

    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or applicable laws. We encourage you to review this page periodically for the latest information on our privacy practices.</p>

